Edge computing shifts data processing from centralized cloud servers to the network periphery, closer to data sources like IoT sensors. This proximity minimizes latency, conserves network bandwidth, and enhances data privacy. However, distributing computing nodes across multiple sites complicates security patch management and increases physical vulnerability.', NULL, NULL, 'Edge computing processes data near its source rather than in distant clouds. This reduces response latency and bandwidth usage. The main trade-off is the heightened security and maintenance complexity of distributed nodes.', 
    'Provide a brief summary containing the core definitions and quantitative figures mentioned in the text.', NULL, 'Passage Recall', 'Written Reconstruction', 
