    'NQT-0290', 'If log_2(x) + log_4(x) + log_16(x) = 21, find the value of x.', NULL, '[{"id": "A", "text": "4096"}, {"id": "B", "text": "4092"}, {"id": "C", "text": "4128"}, {"id": "D", "text": "8192"}]'::jsonb, 'A', 
    'Step-by-step Solution:

Step 1: Simplify bases: log_2(x) + (1/2)*log_2(x) + (1/4)*log_2(x) = 21.
Step 2: (7/4) * log_2(x) = 21 => log_2(x) = 12 => x = 4096.', NULL, 'Surds and Indices', 'Logarithmic Equations', 
    'Hard'::nqt_difficulty, 'Advanced Quantitative and Reasoning Ability'::nqt_section, 'MCQ'::nqt_question_type, 110, 
    'Forgetting the base conversions in logarithms.', ARRAY['surds-and-indices', 'advanced-aptitude']::text[], 'Inspired'::nqt_source_type, 2024, 3, TRUE
);

